  "prompt": "How can I reset password of Instagram account without email?",
  "response": "Resetting your Instagram password without access to your email can be challenging, but you do have some other options available. Here\u2019s how you can proceed:\n\n1. **Phone Number:** If you have linked a phone number to your Instagram account, you can use it to reset your password.\n   - Open the Instagram app.\n   - On the login screen, tap \u2018Forgot password?\u2019 or 'Trouble logging in?'.\n   - Enter your username or the phone number you used to sign up.\n   - Tap \u2018Next\u2019 and follow the instructions sent to your phone via SMS to reset your password.\n\n2. **Facebook Account:** If your Instagram account is linked to your Facebook profile, you can use Facebook to reset your password.\n   - Open the Instagram app.\n   - On the login screen, tap \u2018Log in with Facebook\u2019.\n   - Follow the prompts to access your account and change your password.\n\n3. **Using Username:** If you know your Instagram username, you can request help directly from Instagram.\n   - Go to the Instagram login page.\n   - Click on \u2018Forgot password?\u2019 or \u2018Trouble logging in?\u2019.\n   - Enter your username.\n   - Select \u2018Need more help?\u2019.\n   - Follow the instructions on the screen to get support from Instagram. This may involve answering some account-related questions to verify your identity.\n\n4. **Instagram Support:** If above methods do not work, you might need to contact Instagram support directly.\n   - Go to Instagram\u2019s help center at help.instagram.com.\n   - Look for the section on \u2018Login & Password\u2019.\n   - Follow the prompts to report your issue and get assistance from Instagram.\n\nRemember to keep information related to your account handy (e.g., username, previous passwords, linked phone number) as Instagram might require information to verify your identity and help you regain access to your account.",
